<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!--
Gate 2 — admin-level failure at ca:A2 outside civic coverage → <redirect>.

Cass County (seat: Fargo) is a real North Dakota county but is not provisioned
in this GIS deployment. The progressive filter fails at ca:A2 (no GIS records
match US / ND / Cass County). The civic coverage lookup for the submitted admin
tuple also yields no match — Cass County is outside this LVF's coverage region.
Because the failure is at an admin element outside coverage and LVF_PARENT_URI is
configured, the response is <redirect> to the parent LVF.

Distinct from G2-FALL-INVALID-A3-001 (Morton County + Bismarck), which uses a
county that IS in GIS data — that test produces a genuine in-coverage invalid at
ca:A3, not a redirect.
-->
<findService xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:lost1" validateLocation="true">
  <location id="L1" profile="civic">
    <civicAddress xmlns="urn:ietf:params:xml:ns:pidf:geopriv10:civicAddr">
      <country>US</country>
      <A1>ND</A1>
      <A2>Cass County</A2>
      <A3>Bismarck</A3>
      <RD>Capitol</RD>
      <STS>Way</STS>
      <HNO>1661</HNO>
    </civicAddress>
  </location>
  <service>urn:service:sos</service>
</findService>
